"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-26-fresh-dressage-abuse-claim-olympic-rider-accused-hitting-horse-21300516\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"A second Olympic rider is facing allegations of equine abuse asAustria's Max Kuhner has been accused of hitting a horse's legs with a bar in order to make it jump higher.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 73, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"score\": 0.6542913736601556, \"rank\": 0.5282066398277045, \"text\": \"Max\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A second Olympic rider\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 22}, {\"ngram\": \"allegations\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 44}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse's legs\", \"from\": 112, \"to\": 126}, {\"ngram\": \"a bar\", \"from\": 132, \"to\": 137}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just days after Team GB's Charlotte Dujardin was forced to withdraw from the Olympics over a video that showed her repeatedly striking a horse with a whip, Kuhner, who is ranked third in the world and is in contention to win a medal inParis, has been forced to deny allegations of abuse towards a horse in May 2023.\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 188, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.8753331990685809, \"rank\": 0.08875724061158848, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 198, \"end\": 216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 257}, {\"ngram\": \"a video\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 314}, {\"ngram\": \"a whip\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 334}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 368}, {\"ngram\": \"contention\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 389}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal inParis\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"allegations\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 449}, {\"ngram\": \"abuse\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 474}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After obtaining information from a whistleblower, PETA, the animal rights organisation, filed a criminal complaint against Kuhner with the Munich II public prosecutor's office last September.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"information\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"a whistleblower, PETA\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"the animal rights organisation\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"a criminal complaint\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 603}, {\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 612, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"the Munich II public prosecutor's office\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Penal orders against Kuhner and a second person working as a trainer were issued in March this year.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Penal orders\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"a second person\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"a trainer\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 749}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kuhner is accused of using a forbidden training method known as 'barring' in which a wooden or metal bar is placed over an obstacle so that it hits the horse's legs and forces the animal to pull them higher when it jumps.\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 1004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"a forbidden training method\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 837}, {\"ngram\": \"a wooden or metal bar\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"an obstacle\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse's legs\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 947}, {\"ngram\": \"the animal\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The practice, which is alleged to have taken place at Kuhner's training stable in Starnberg, Germany, is banned by the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI) and is considered as abuse towards the horses.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starnberg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5471387887030696e-27, \"text\": \"Starnberg\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starnberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starnberg\"}, {\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.6059456502390715, \"rank\": 0.647511917044334, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7294170715542395e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The practice\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"the International Federation\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1149}, {\"ngram\": \"Equestrian Sports\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"abuse\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"the horses\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kuhner, 50, has denied the allegations and a request has been made to discontinue the proceedings.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"the allegations\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"a request\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"the proceedings\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'These are accusations that have no basis whatsoever,' he said in a statement to the APA on Thursday.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Psychiatric_Association\", \"score\": 0.9864194677902153, \"rank\": 0.013767502212695414, \"text\": \"APA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Psychiatric_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Psychiatric_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"accusations\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1348}, {\"ngram\": \"no basis\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1367}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1426}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'In contrast, we can prove through official veterinary certificates, experts and many witnesses that our horses have always been and are doing well.\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contrast\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1441}, {\"ngram\": \"official veterinary certificates\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1496}, {\"ngram\": \"experts\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"many witnesses\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"our horses\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Animal welfare is our top priority and our entire operation is geared towards this around the clock.'\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1679, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Animal welfare\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"our top priority\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1612}, {\"ngram\": \"our entire operation\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"the clock\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Austrian Equestrian Federation (OEPS) has also backed Kuhner.\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.9989259335594263, \"rank\": 0.0010316035339109765, \"text\": \"Austrian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"OEPS\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1721}, {\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1745}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The OEPS can confirm, based on all observations during the years of working with Max Kuhner, that the keeping, training and presentation of his horses is of the highest quality,' a statement from the OEPS read.\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1830, \"end\": 1833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"score\": 0.6542913736601556, \"rank\": 0.5282066398277045, \"text\": \"Max\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The OEPS\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"all observations\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"the keeping\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"presentation\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"his horses\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1899}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest quality\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1939}, {\"ngram\": \"the OEPS read\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Due to his impeccable attitude towards his horse as a sports partner, there is no reason whatsoever to assume that he uses methods in training that are contrary to animal welfare, or has used them in the past.'\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2172, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his impeccable attitude\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"his horse\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2010}, {\"ngram\": \"a sports partner\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"no reason\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"methods\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"animal welfare\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elisabeth Max-Theurer, the vice president of the Austrian Olympic Committee and OEPS president, also criticised the length of the investigation into Kuhner, who is set to appear at the Olympics for the first time in his career.\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elisabeth_Theurer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elisabeth Max-Theurer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elisabeth_Theurer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elisabeth_Theurer\"}, {\"begin\": 2223, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austrian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Austrian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austrian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austrian_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the vice president\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"OEPS president\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2268}, {\"ngram\": \"the length\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2296}, {\"ngram\": \"the investigation\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2317}, {\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2329}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2386}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It is clear that an investigation is necessary,' she said.\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'In Max's case, the situation is unclear and we have to wait to see whether a hearing takes place.'\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2468, \"end\": 2471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"score\": 0.6542913736601556, \"rank\": 0.5282066398277045, \"text\": \"Max\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2493}, {\"ngram\": \"a hearing\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2549}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2556, \"to\": 2561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked why there has been no attempt to clarify the allegations before the Olympics, Max-Theurer said: 'This was deliberately spread and done quite deliberately.\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no attempt\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2600}, {\"ngram\": \"the allegations\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2627}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2647}, {\"ngram\": \"Max-Theurer\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps it is also because people are jealous of Max because he is number three in the world and has an absolute chance of winning a medal.'\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2775, \"end\": 2778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"score\": 0.6542913736601556, \"rank\": 0.5282066398277045, \"text\": \"Max\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2753, \"to\": 2759}, {\"ngram\": \"number\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2799}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2818}, {\"ngram\": \"an absolute chance\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 2864}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The FEI's chief veterinarian, Dr. Gotan Akerstrom, said on Thursday: 'We have heard about the legal proceedings in Germany and are currently gathering information.'\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 3032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2872, \"end\": 2875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7294170715542395e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.6059456502390715, \"rank\": 0.647511917044334, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dr. Gotan Akerstrom\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2917}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2935}, {\"ngram\": \"the legal proceedings\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 2979}, {\"ngram\": \"information\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3030}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kuhner has previously been accused of animal cruelty in 2008 where videos captured on a mobile phone allegedly showed him jumping a horse over a wire at a water obstacle.\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kuhner\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3040}, {\"ngram\": \"animal cruelty\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3086}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3107}, {\"ngram\": \"a mobile phone\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3134}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 3164, \"to\": 3171}, {\"ngram\": \"a wire\", \"from\": 3177, \"to\": 3183}, {\"ngram\": \"a water obstacle\", \"from\": 3187, \"to\": 3203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Bavarian Riding and Driving Association conducted an investigation but while the disciplinary commission criticised Kuhner's training method it was unable to find behaviour that violated animal welfare laws and the case was discontinued due to 'minor guilt'.\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3210, \"end\": 3218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bavaria\", \"score\": 0.9986405249209102, \"rank\": 0.001059134890525332, \"text\": \"Bavarian\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bavaria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bavaria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3276}, {\"ngram\": \"the disciplinary commission\", \"from\": 3287, \"to\": 3314}, {\"ngram\": \"Kuhner's training method\", \"from\": 3326, \"to\": 3350}, {\"ngram\": \"behaviour\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"animal welfare laws\", \"from\": 3397, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 3421, \"to\": 3429}, {\"ngram\": \"minor guilt\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3518, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more stories\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3486}, {\"ngram\": \"our sport page\", \"from\": 3503, \